{"_type":"issue","id":"risinggo-9nn","title":"Implement Streamable HTTP transport + Health/Readiness endpoints in Server","description":"The Basic MCP Server Bootstrap bead (risinggo-kco) is closed but current code in cmd/server/main.go:35 and internal/mcp/server.go:226 only supports stdio via Run+StdioTransport. Config supports TRANSPORT=streamable-http and HTTP_PORT but is ignored. k6 loadtest (risinggo-fle) and health bead (risinggo-8hd) cannot proceed without HTTP /mcp endpoint using NewStreamableHTTPHandler and separate health handlers for /healthz (liveness) and /readyz (DB pool + ready). Also implement graceful shutdown for http.Server to honor the closed graceful shutdown bead. Add support in Server.Start() and main for dual transport based on cfg. This unblocks P0 load test and P1 health.","notes":"Code complete: Server now supports TRANSPORT=streamable-http with NewStreamableHTTPHandler mounted at /mcp (for k6 compat), plus /healthz (always healthy) and /readyz (DB ping check). Config updated to support MCP_* and RISINGWAVE_CONNECTION_STR from docker-compose. Main uses ctx for Run/ListenAndServe + graceful shutdown on signal. Pool.Ping exposed. Verified: go build, go test ./..., go vet all pass. Unblocks health and load test beads.","status":"in_progress","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Shailendra Thakur","owner":"llearnell@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-29T06:18:08Z","created_by":"Shailendra Thakur","updated_at":"2026-05-29T06:20:49Z","started_at":"2026-05-29T06:18:12Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":2,"comment_count":0}
